{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:07:00.430Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777684020042_0","status":"success","output":"commit e8e7e5394fcf1e08597b184886d3241936a20011\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 15:08:27 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(image_api): CT Marketing image-generation REST surface (#21, #22, #23)\n    \n    New package src/cypherclaw/image_api/ implementing the contract in\n    specs/external/cypherclaw-image-contract.md:\n      - POST /api/v1/jobs   — submit spec_yaml (Shape A or B), returns job_id\n      - GET  /api/v1/jobs/{job_id} — poll status, returns output_urls when complete\n      - GET  /healthz       — liveness\n    \n    Modules:\n      - schemas.py           Pydantic SubmitRequest/SubmitResponse/StatusResponse\n                             + InternalSpec normalized form + JobStatus enum\n      - spec_parser.py       parse Shape A (explicit prompt) and Shape B\n                             (content-derived from title + description) into\n                             InternalSpec. Deterministic prompt template, no LLM.\n      - jobs_db.py           SQLite job state at /home/user/cypherclaw-data/\n                             image_jobs.db. WAL mode, thread-safe per-call conns.\n                             Lifecycle: queued → running → uploading → terminal.\n      - gemini_backend.py    google-genai wrapper with model override support;\n                             default gemini-3-pro-image-preview (Nano Banana Pro);\n                             lazy SDK import so tests inject fakes cleanly.\n      - s3_uploader.py       boto3 wrapper, scoped to PutObject on jobs/* prefix;\n                             returns direct S3 HTTPS URL.\n      - worker.py            sync core process_job_sync + async schedule_job;\n                             WorkerHooks injection seam for tests.\n      - app.py               FastAPI factory create_app(s, db, hooks) — no module\n                             singleton so importing the package never touches the\n                             filesystem (clean test ergonomics).\n      - __main__.py          uvicorn entry: `python -m cypherclaw.image_api`\n      - config.py            env-var Settings dataclass with from_env classmethod\n    \n    Systemd unit: my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-image-api.service\n      - User=user, EnvironmentFile=/home/user/cypherclaw/.env (AWS keys)\n      - Restart=always with backoff; hardened (NoNewPrivileges, ProtectSystem,\n        ReadWritePaths=/home/user/cypherclaw-data only)\n      - Default port 9000, host 0.0.0.0 (tailnet-bound only at deploy)\n    \n    Tests (51 new, all passing locally; 3264 total still green):\n      - test_image_api_spec_parser   Shape A + B + project-slug coherence + errors\n      - test_image_api_jobs_db       insert/get/update lifecycle, list_pending,\n                                     persistence across reopen, parent-dir create\n      - test_image_api_s3_uploader   FakeS3Client; URL format, put_object args,\n                                     alt region/prefix, default content-type\n      - test_image_api_worker        full lifecycle with mocked Gemini + S3,\n                                     Gemini refusal → failed, upload fail → failed,\n                                     idempotent on terminal jobs, ordering checks\n      - test_image_api_app           FastAPI TestClient end-to-end: 202 + job_id,\n                                     polling to completed, Shape B accepted,\n                                     400 on no-prompt, 404 on unknown id,\n                                     failure path surfaces error in poll\n    \n    Tasks #21 (package), #22 (TDD suite), #23 (systemd unit) complete.\n    Tasks #20 (AWS bucket+IAM) and #24 (deploy + smoke test) still pending —\n    #20 needs admin AWS creds, #24 needs #20 to land first.\n\nsrc/cypherclaw/image_api/__main__.py"}
